,"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"377f336f45e3eb50b3b50c15961f9b4aff559f2e8069fbd7c15d5af61b9133b7","event_uuid":"135bfeea-063c-40f0-aafa-88ac62e60d7d","position":{"commit_sha":"706b617988083c37a9aa2660f99fa2b79200e7f5","position":"1784745100977638001-135bfeea-063c-40f0-aafa-88ac62e60d7d"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"23879da8657edf93433c3ed5f211fdaaaa77600a87ac5b73bb05a82ec216b02d","event_uuid":"823e2ae5-ac71-4b45-8f82-3426a5a27127","position":{"commit_sha":"c72d01fb9186ccacd0639317c6d8c8d2d625b8c1","position":"1784745130964359001-823e2ae5-ac71-4b45-8f82-3426a5a27127"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"229907fa2cfebd8400ff89aba268f0586f673496950f137ad8756b1e29cd213e","event_uuid":"95856b97-d006-48b1-962c-90f8bc1719cc","position":{"commit_sha":"b71c4a75b0bec3f03b6991cf7d2e72380263b0bf","position":"1784745463862793427-95856b97-d006-48b1-962c-90f8bc1719cc"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-217_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"a3ceafdb-88fe-4810-a757-5436de84190d","comments":[],"created_at":1784744213437804001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"823e2ae5-ac71-4b45-8f82-3426a5a27127","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"563c-f018-c132-49f0"}],"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nThe `rebar-implement` skill (`examples/agent-skills/rebar-implement/SKILL.md`) dispatches an\nimplementation subagent in Phase 4d but never specifies a model tier. In both Claude Code and\nCodex CLI an unset model inherits the orchestrator's (expensive) model, so the subagent silently\nruns on the strongest tier — the anti-pattern that erases any token saving. The skill also lacks\nguidance on which work is safe to delegate to a cheaper model and how to escalate when a cheap\nimplementer is insufficient.\n\n## Approach\n\nAdd a `## Model tiering` operating principle and targeted amendments to Phases 3, 4a, 4d, plus a\nnew `### 4e-bis` escalation ladder. Frame tiers as *capabilities* (strong / standard / cheap)\nwith Claude Code and Codex CLI example mappings, rather than hardcoding product names — the skill\nis cross-harness (`AGENTS.md`-class prose read by non-Claude harnesses) and model names drift\nacross releases. The held-out-TDD invariant is preserved: test-authoring (4b) and held-out\nvalidation (4e, already in the file) stay strong-tier, and a *separate* implementer always\nexists, so a green result still means the implementer could not tailor code to the full oracle.\nThe design was pressure-tested across five adversarial review rounds before this change.\n\nRejected alternative: naming Opus/Sonnet/Haiku directly — simpler but breaks portability to\nCodex and rots as models are renamed.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `examples/agent-skills/rebar-implement/SKILL.md` — the only file changed; prose-only\n  (~+111/-2 lines). No source code, no behavior, no tests.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A `## Model tiering` section exists with a capability-tier table naming both a Claude Code\n      and a Codex CLI example per tier — checked by `grep -n 'Model tiering' && grep -c '^| '`.\n- [ ] Phase 4d states a standard-tier default, a cheap-tier-only-for-transcription rule, and a\n      constraints-in-brief requirement — checked by reading section 4d.\n- [ ] A `### 4e-bis` escalation ladder exists that distinguishes normal held-out iteration\n      (no escalation) from the model-weakness escalation triggers — checked by reading it.\n- [ ] No hardcoded module-size number is introduced; the brief cites\n      `.github/module-size-limit.txt` (which contains `800`) as the source of truth — checked by\n      grep for the filename in SKILL.md.\n- [ ] Phase 3 dispatch-by-kind includes a seam note directing research/discovery/grep-shaped\n      non-code leaves to the cheap/fast tier — checked by grep for \"tier\" within the Phase 3\n      non-code-leaf bullet.\n- [ ] Phase 4a carries an explicit annotation that the existing-coverage search is cheap-shaped\n      but spec derivation stays strong-tier by choice — checked by reading Phase 4a.\n- [ ] Change is docs-only and `make lint` passes — checked by `git diff --stat` showing only the\n      SKILL.md path and a clean lint run.\n\nNo `## Testing` section: this is a prose/docs change with no new testable behavior. \"Transcription\"\nin AC2 means a leaf whose happy-path test fully pins the code (1–2 files), so implementing it is\nmechanical transcription rather than design.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"examples/agent-skills/rebar-implement/SKILL.md","reason":"Add Model tiering section, Phase 4d tier defaults, 4e-bis escalation ladder, Phase 3/4a seam notes"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["relates_to","563c-f018-c132-49f0"]],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"320935e3-d39f-4d2c-a470-50f9c74cd1d6","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"6375-f80b-00ea-4083","ticket_type":"task","title":"rebar-implement skill: capability-tiered model delegation (strong orchestrator / cheaper subagents)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["1e3d50a7-c6a6-4d15-815f-be5408b7face","454c2434-3799-4e4f-83ca-b7261d1420cb","c286dff6-1088-46dc-b7fd-3b651f0fbac2","7ecee1a7-a4d4-4ad7-a2a8-c07c612f9116","320935e3-d39f-4d2c-a470-50f9c74cd1d6","135bfeea-063c-40f0-aafa-88ac62e60d7d","823e2ae5-ac71-4b45-8f82-3426a5a27127","95856b97-d006-48b1-962c-90f8bc1719cc"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784745463862793428,"uuid":"344031e2-3ea4-43b0-887b-d5e2c375a33b"}